http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Awareness-campaign-against-smoking/article13978210.ece

The Regional Cancer Centre (RCC) and the Directorate of Higher Secondary Education will be jointly organising CATCH (Crusade Against Tobacco Consumption in Higher secondary schools), an awareness campaign against smoking.The programme is being organised in view of a study conducted by the National Sample Survey Organisation (NSSO) in which it was found that 80 per cent of smokers get that habit before they are 18 years old and that this habit is more prevalent among children from coastal areas.The programme aims at creating awareness on the negative effects of smoking among students in government and aided higher secondary schools in coastal areas. The pilot programme will be launched in Kollam district. It will then be implemented in Alappuzha and Thiruvananthapuram districts.